==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: combinatory
<hw>combinatory</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>able to combine; tending to combine.</def> <note>same
as <er>combinative</er>, 2.</note> [Narrower terms: <stype>integrative
(vs. disintegrative)</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> combinative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or relating to combinations.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>combinative (vs. noncombinative)</stype>] <source>WordNet
1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>produced by a process of combining; <as>as, a
<ex>combinatorial</ex> explosion of possibilities</as>; -- used
especially in reference to mathematical or statistical processes of
computing possible combinations.</def>⟦br⟧
<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>combinatory</ent>⟦br⟧

